<body>
    <h1>Uploading a eZ Publish site to the cloud</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>This is a step-by-step guide on how to upload your eZ Publish in=
stallation to the cloud for the first time</p>
<h1 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-Ensureyoumeettherequirements">E=
nsure you meet the requirements</h1>
<p>In order to upload a eZ Publish to the cloud, these conditions needs to =
be met:</p>
<ul>
<li><span>Make sure you comply with the<a href=3D"/display/EZPCLOUD/eZ+Publ=
ish+Cloud+-Beta-+Whitelist"> eZ Publish Cloud Whitelist</a></span></li>
<li>You need a work installation of eZ Publish running locally
<ul>
<li>Your local eZ Publish installation must have the <a href=3D"/display/EZ=
PCLOUD/eZ+Cloud+extension">eZ Cloud extension</a> installed</li>
</ul></li>
<li>You need access to the cloud administration interface:&nbsp;<a href=3D"=
http://cloud.ez.no" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://admin.c=
loud.ez.no</a></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Your account nee=
ds to have a SSH key associated with your account</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Basic knowledge =
about SSH, Git and SFTP</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">A Git and SFTP c=
lient installed locally</span><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height:=
 13.0pt;"><br /></span></li>
</ul>
<div>
For the examples below, we assume you are on a unix based system with Git, =
openssh's SFTP client, mysqldump and=20
<code>rsync</code> installed
</div>
<h2 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-HowtocheckthatyouhaveaSSHkey">H=
ow to check that you have a SSH key</h2>
<p><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">&nbsp;This is the=
 procedure for checking that you have a SSH key associated with your cloud =
account</span></p>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Log in to&nbsp;<=
a href=3D"http://admin.cloud.ez.no" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">http://admin.cloud.ez.no</a></span></li>
<li>The frontpage will show you the list of environments you have access to=
</li>
<li>Click on the environment you want to inspect</li>
<li>Click the &quot;Manage Users&quot; button (not all users have this butt=
on, just &quot;OWNER&quot;. All users might go to <a href=3D"http://login.e=
z.no" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">login.ez.no</a> and find the=
ir key, if it was uploaded, in the corresponding field in their profile)</l=
i>
<li>Your user should then be listed, including information about your SSH k=
ey</li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-UploadaSSHkeytoyouraccount">Upl=
oad a SSH key to your account</h2>
<p><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">If you do not hav=
e a SSH key associated with your account, this is how to upload it</span></=
p>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Log in to&nbsp;<=
a href=3D"http://share.ez.no" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http=
://share.ez.no</a></span></li>
<li>Edit your profile on :&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/community/pro=
file" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://share.ez.no/community=
/profile</a></li>
<li>Click on &quot;Edit account&quot; button (<strong>do not confuse this w=
ith the &quot;Edit profile&quot; button</strong>)</li>
<li><p>Cut and paste in your public SSH in the &quot;Public key (openSSH fo=
rmat only&quot; field )<br />The format of the key should look like:<br />s=
sh-rsa ABC......=3D emailaddress@example.com</p></li>
<li>Save your changes</li>
<li>Log out of&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://admin.cloud.ez.no" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://admin.cloud.ez.no</a>&nbsp;(if you where logg=
ed in)</li>
<li>Log in again on&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://admin.cloud.ez.no" class=3D"exte=
rnal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://admin.cloud.ez.no</a></li>
<li>Follow the steps explained in the &quot;How to check that you have a SS=
H key&quot; chapter</li>
</ol>
<h1 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-ObtainlogininformationtoStagear=
ea,GitandSFTP">Obtain login information to Stage area, Git and SFTP</h1>
<p>This is how you get login information for Git and SFTP</p>
<ol>
<li>Log in to&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://admin.cloud.ez.no" class=3D"external-l=
ink" rel=3D"nofollow">http://admin.cloud.ez.no</a></li>
<li>The frontpage will show you the list of environments you have access to=
</li>
<li>Click on the environment you want to inspect</li>
<li>Click the &quot;Show Details&quot; link</li>
<li>Login information about how to access sites in stage and rollback state=
 is displayed</li>
<li>Login information about how to access Git is displayed</li>
<li>Login information about how to access SFTP is displayed on the format :=
 username@ftphostname:portno</li>
</ol>
<h1 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-Uploadyourinstallationtotheclou=
d">Upload your installation to the cloud</h1>
<p>This is the overview on how to upload your installation to the cloud:</p=
>
<ul>
<li>your code ( ezpublish + extensions + settings ) must be uploaded to the=
 git repository</li>
<li>Your database and content files ( like images) must be uploaded to the =
SFTP server</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-UploadingyourcodetoGit">Uploadi=
ng your code to Git</h2>
<p>The example below will assume</p>
<ul>
<li>you have your eZ Publish site locally in <code>/var/www/mysite.com</cod=
e></li>
<li>your git repository is located at&nbsp;<code>mysite@git.ez.cloud.ixonos=
.com:ez.git</code></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-ClonetheGitrepository">Clone th=
e Git repository</h3>
<p>You can clone the Git repository by running the following:</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>$cd ~
$git clone mysite@git.ez.cloud.ixonos.com:ez.git mysite</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Copy your eZ Publish site to the Git directory (except the var/ director=
y):</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>$rsync -av --filter=3D&quot;+ /.htaccess*&quot; --filter=3D&quot;- .**=
&quot; --filter &quot;- /var&quot; /var/www/mysite.com/ ~/mysite/</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-Pushyourcodetogit">Push your co=
de to git</h3>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>$cd ~/mysite
$git add .
$git commit
$git push origin master</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-TagthecodeinGit">Tag the code i=
n Git</h3>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>$cd ~/mysite

$git tag mysite-v1.0
$git push origin mysite-v1.0</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-Uploadyourdatabaseandvar/direct=
oryviaSFTP">Upload your database and var/ directory via SFTP</h2>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-MaketheDBdump">Make the DB dump=
</h3>
<p>Use mysqldump to create a dump like this:</p>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>$cd /tmp
$mysqldump -u [username ]-p [database] &gt; mysite-v1.0.sql</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>( replace username and database name according to your system )</p>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-UploadtheDBtoSFTP">Upload the D=
B to SFTP</h3>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>cd /tmp
$sftp -P [portno] [username]@hostname
SFTP&gt; cd db
SFTP&gt; put mysite-v1.0.sql
SFTP&gt; exit
$rm /tmp/mysite-v1.0.sql</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-Makethevar/dump">Make the var/ =
dump</h3>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>$cd /var/www/mysite.com/var
$tar -czf /tmp/mysite-v1.0.tar.gz ezwebin_site storage</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The example above assumes your vardir is named &quot;ezwebin_site&quot;.=
 It might be called something else on your system</p>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-UploadthevardumptoSFTP">Upload =
the var dump to SFTP</h3>
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>$cd /tmp
$sftp -P [portno] [username]@hostname
SFTP&gt; cd var
SFTP&gt; put mysite-v1.0.tar.gz
SFTP&gt; exit
$rm mysite-v1.0.tar.gz</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-Stageyourinstallation">Stage yo=
ur installation</h2>
<ol>
<li>Log in to <a href=3D"http://admin.cloud.ez.no" class=3D"external-link" =
rel=3D"nofollow">http://admin.cloud.ez.no</a></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">The frontpage wi=
ll show you the list of environments you have access to</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Click on the env=
ironment you want to stage</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Click the &quot;=
Edit&quot; button</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-SoftwareRepository">Software Re=
pository</h3>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Click &quot;New =
Deployment&quot; link</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Provide a &quot;=
Deployment name&quot; and check the git tag &quot;<code>mysite-v1.0</code>&=
quot;</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">Click &quot;Next=
 step&quot; button</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-eZPublishVersion">eZ Publish Ve=
rsion</h3>
<ol>
<li>Select &quot;eZ Publish 4.7&quot; in the version drop down</li>
<li>Click &quot;Next Step&quot; button</li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-DatabaseandFileImport">Database=
 and File Import</h3>
<ol>
<li>Click the checkbox &quot;I would like to create a new database from the=
 database dump and import the corresponding files.&quot;</li>
<li>Click the checkbox &quot;<code>mysite-v1.0.sql</code>&quot;</li>
<li>Click the checkbox &quot;<code>mysite-v1.0.tar.gz</code>&quot;</li>
<li>Click &quot;Next Step&quot; button</li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"UploadingaeZPublishsitetothecloud-Review">Review</h3>
<ol>
<li>Review your configuration</li>
<li>Click &quot;Create Deployment&quot; button</li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
